# Shared build-context ignore for BOTH images built from the repo root:
#   - Dockerfile        -> the bitcoind node image (needs Dockerfile + entrypoint)
#   - tools.Dockerfile  -> the three Rust tools (needs the Cargo workspace)
#
# Allowlist only what those builds COPY; everything else (.git, and the Rust
# target/ dirs that reach GBs after local builds) stays out of the upload.
#
# Under BuildKit, tools.Dockerfile.dockerignore overrides this file for the
# tools image. The classic builder ignores per-Dockerfile files, so this root
# file must cover both images on its own — hence the Rust allowlist entries.
*
!Dockerfile
!docker-entrypoint.sh
!Cargo.toml
!Cargo.lock
!.cargo
!crates
